\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 10. C. salvifolius} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 524 (1753). Stems up to 100 cm, spreading or procumbent. Leaves 10-40 × 6-20 mm, ovate or elliptical, rounded or broadly cuneate at base, green, scabrid and rugose above, with stellate hairs on both surfaces, petiolate. Flowers mostly solitary but sometimes up to 4 in a cyme, petiolate. Pedicels 10-100 mm. Sepals 5, the two outer cordate at base. Flowers 3-5 cm in diameter, white. Style very short. 2n = 18.{\i  S. Europe, extending northwards to} c. 47°{\i  in W. France.} Al Bl Bu Co Cr Ga Gr He Hs It Ju Lu Sa Si Tu.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 11. C. populifolius} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 523 (1753). Stems up to 150 cm, somewhat spreading. Leaves 40-100 × 30-65 mm, ovate, cordate at base, glabrous, green and smooth above, petiolate. Cymes 2- to 6-flowered, pedunculate. Sepals 5, the two outer cordate at base. Flowers 4-6 cm in diameter, white. Style very short. 2n = 18.{\i  Spain and Portugal, extending eastwards to} c. 3° {\i E in S. France}. Ga Hs Lu.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b a}) Subsp. {\b populifolius}: Leaves usually at least 1½ times as long as wide, not or scarcely undulate. Sepals with few white hairs. •{\i  France, N. Spain, Portugal}.
