\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 12. C. laurifolius} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 523 (1753). Stems up to 150 cm, erect. Leaves 30-80(-90) × 10-30 mm, ovate to ovate-lanceolate, 3-veined, dark green and glabrous on upper surface, densely white-tomentose beneath, petiolate. Inflorescence a terminal (1-)4- to 8-flowered, long-pedunculate, umbel-like cyme, often with 1 or 2 opposite pairs of flowers below. Sepals 3. Flowers 5-6 cm in diameter, white. Style very short. 2n = 18. {\i  S.W. Europe, extending to W.C. Italy}.  Co Ga Hs It Lu.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 13. C. ladanifer} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 523 (1753). Stems up to 250 cm, erect, very viscid. Leaves 40-80(-120) × 6-25 mm, linear-lanceolate, 3-veined for 1/3 their length, green and glabrous above, densely white-tomentose beneath, subsessile. Sepals 3. Flowers 7-10 cm in diameter, solitary, white, with or without a crimson spot at the base of each petal. Style very short. Ovary 10-locular.{\i  S.W. Europe. }Ga Hs Lu.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 14. C. palhinhae} Ingram, {\i Gard. Chron.} ser. 3, {\b 114}: 34 (1943). Like {\b 13} but stems only up to 50 cm; leaves 20-60 mm, oblanceolate to spathulate; flowers white, unspotted; ovary 6-locular. •{\i  S.W. Portugal} ({\i W. coast of Algarve}). Lu.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 15. C. clusii} Dunal in DC.,{\i  Prodr.}{\b  1}: 266 (1824) ({\i C. libanotis} auct. mult., non L.). Stems up to 100 cm, erect, much-branched. Leaves 10-25 × 1-2 mm, linear, dark green above, white-tomentose beneath, with revolute margins, subsessile. Inflorescence up to 12-flowered with a terminal, umbel-like cyme and often with opposite pairs of flowers or 3-flowered cymes below. Peduncles, pedicels and calyx clothed with long, white hairs. Sepals 3, 5-8 mm. Flowers 2-3 cm in diameter, white. Style short. {\i W. & C. Mediterranean region, from S. Spain to S.E. Italy.} Bl Hs It Si.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 16. C. libanotis} L.,{\i  Syst. Nat.} ed. 10,{\b  2}: 1077 (1759) ({\i C. bourgaeanus} Cosson). Like {\b 15} but leaves (15-)20-35(-40) × 1·5-3 mm; peduncles, pedicels and calyx subglabrous, viscid; sepals 8-10 mm.{\i  S.W. Portugal, S.W. Spain.} Hs Lu.
