\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. H. ocymoides} (Lam.) Willk. in Willk. & Lange,{\i  Prodr. Fl. Hisp.}{\b  3}: 715 (1878) ({\i Helianthemum ocymoides} (Lam.) Pers.). Erect, rarely procumbent, up to 100 cm. Leaves of non-flowering shoots 3-15 × 2-5 mm, obovate, grey-tomentose, with 1-3 veins, shortly petiolate, often plicate; leaves of flowering shoots 12-30 × 3·5-7·5 mm, obovate to lanceolate, green, with 3 veins, sessile. Flowers on long pedicels, in lax, terminal panicles. Sepals 3; petals yellow, usually with a dark spot at the base. 2n = 18.{\i  Iberian peninsula, chiefly in the centre and west.} Hs Lu.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. H. alyssoides} (Lam.) C. Koch,{\i  Hort. Dendrol. }32 (1853) ({\i H. occidentale} Willk., {\i Helianthemum alyssoides} (Lam.) Vent.). Compact, erect or decumbent, 10-100 cm, grey-tomentose. Leaves 5-40 × 3-15 mm, oblong to ovate- or obovate-lanceolate, obtuse, dark green above, white-tomentose beneath, or white-stellate-tomentose on both surfaces; shortly petiolate or sessile. Flowers in short, terminal, shortly villous cymes. Sepals 3, shortly villous; petals yellow, unspotted. •{\i  W. & C. France, N.W. Spain, N. & C. Portugal}. Ga Hs Lu.
\par

